Auto managed configurations can now declare a "public static ManagedConfig mc;" in an APSConfig subclass and call isManaged() and waitUntilManaged() on it to ensure it has been populated with config values before using it.

Now also updated lastUsed timestamp on saveObject() and retrieveObject().

- Restructured project structure. - Removed category APS-Enterprise. - Added category APS-Auth and APS-Data. - APSSimpleUserService moved to APS-Auth. - APSDataSource and APSOpenJPAProvider moved to APS-Data. - No longer any subcategory APIs. All APIs reside in APS-APIs.

Removed non working profile to update version.
~/.aps/apsfs is now the default root for APSFilesystemService if aps.filesystem.root system property is not set.

Moved connect() and disconnect() code from activator to service provider with delayed connect until first service call due to that connect does things that cannot be done at activation. The previous code created a server startup deadlock situation where in activation we were waiting for something that would not happen until activation was done. The server deploys bundles sequentially without activation timeout ...
